02:13:04,990 --> 02:13:06,920
You can do? You can do?

2963
02:13:06,920 --> 02:13:08,460
That's amazing.

2964
02:13:07,420 --> 02:13:08,460
You can do your best.

2965
02:13:08,460 --> 02:13:10,130
I see. You can do your best.

2966
02:13:10,130 --> 02:13:12,260
If you try you can accomplish it, Riri.

2967
02:13:12,360 --> 02:13:14,700
Do your best. High-five.

2968
02:13:14,700 --> 02:13:15,930
Off you go.

2969
02:13:15,930 --> 02:13:19,100
She did it. Yes, she did. She did her best.

2970
02:13:19,600 --> 02:13:22,140
And for the 3 O'clock tea time...

2971
02:13:22,140 --> 02:13:25,640
And also the bandages to protect her fathers fingers.

2972
02:13:25,640 --> 02:13:29,150
She has arrived at the drug store.

2973
02:13:29,510 --> 02:13:31,950
Here there's also a specialty corner.

2974
02:13:31,950 --> 02:13:34,450
Since everyone is preparing kaki these days.

2975
02:13:34,450 --> 02:13:37,350
A line-up with great additions for their tea break.

2976
02:13:37,350 --> 02:13:42,660
She was asked to get anko dango but they are sold out.

2977
02:13:44,160 --> 02:13:47,970
But there's anko in these too so they will do.

2978
02:13:47,970 --> 02:13:50,400
It's hard to make such a decision.

2979
02:13:55,770 --> 02:13:59,510
While considering it she gets the bandages first.

2980
02:13:58,540 --> 02:14:00,540
Remarkable.

2981
02:13:59,510 --> 02:14:01,910
For a guitarist their fingers are their life.

2982
02:14:01,910 --> 02:14:04,110
So he wraps them in bandage.

2983
02:14:04,110 --> 02:14:07,280
She found the bandages right away.

2984
02:14:07,450 --> 02:14:11,320
But she's lost in the many types.

2985
02:14:11,320 --> 02:14:14,190
Which one should I get?

2986
02:14:14,190 --> 02:14:16,730
She can't decide for herself.

2987
02:14:18,400 --> 02:14:22,200
She doesn't know any of the store workers and without asking any

2988
02:14:22,200 --> 02:14:25,940
she leaves the shop without purchasing anything.

2989
02:14:24,700 --> 02:14:26,700
How come?

2990
02:14:26,700 --> 02:14:28,940
She's not confident.

2991
02:14:28,940 --> 02:14:34,010
She has become a Ririka who: Can't do it. Can't do her best.

2992
02:14:52,360 --> 02:14:55,870
Despite completing the errand at the hardware store.

2993
02:14:56,330 --> 02:14:58,840
She carries a sense of defeat.

2994
02:14:58,840 --> 02:15:03,040
And it can be seen on her face as she returns.

2995
02:15:05,110 --> 02:15:08,550
Welcome back. That was quick.

2996
02:15:08,550 --> 02:15:09,750
Welcome back.

2997
02:15:09,750 --> 02:15:10,780
Amazing.

2998
02:15:10,780 --> 02:15:13,520
You bought gloves?

2999
02:15:13,520 --> 02:15:17,960
That's so great.

3000
02:15:14,990 --> 02:15:17,960
Even though she's being praised her face says it all.

3001
02:15:17,290 --> 02:15:19,290
That's expected.

3002
02:15:17,960 --> 02:15:23,430
You went and got some? How great.

3003
02:15:23,430 --> 02:15:26,760
Thank you.

3004
02:15:27,300 --> 02:15:29,330
Huh? Huh?

3005
02:15:29,330 --> 02:15:30,570
What about the dango?

3006
02:15:30,570 --> 02:15:32,270
There it is.

3007
02:15:32,270 --> 02:15:33,570
Did you go to Nakaya?

3008
02:15:33,570 --> 02:15:35,370
She did go but you see...

3009
02:15:35,370 --> 02:15:36,510
They didn't have dango?

3010
02:15:36,510 --> 02:15:38,410
They didn't have dango.

3011
02:15:38,410 --> 02:15:40,540
They only had the soybean ones.

3012
02:15:39,410 --> 02:15:40,540
They only had the soybean ones?

3013
02:15:40,540 --> 02:15:44,120
Then the green ones would've been fine.

3014
02:15:41,810 --> 02:15:45,580
See...you could've gotten the green ones.

3015
02:15:45,820 --> 02:15:48,190
Can you go again?

3016
02:15:47,720 --> 02:15:50,090
She looks so surprised.

3017
02:15:48,990 --> 02:15:50,190
I want to go with papa.

3018
02:15:50,190 --> 02:15:52,420
I'm busy.

3019
02:15:52,420 --> 02:15:53,560
When this is over...

3020
02:15:53,560 --> 02:15:55,230
Ririka can't go.

3021
02:15:55,230 --> 02:15:57,530
She said it clearly.

3022
02:15:58,400 --> 02:15:59,830
I'm tired.

3023
02:15:59,260 --> 02:15:59,830
You're tired?

3024
02:15:59,830 --> 02:16:02,100
But she's not exhausted yet.

3025
02:16:03,500 --> 02:16:05,100
I'm tired.

3026
02:16:05,100 --> 02:16:06,670
He's a father who

3027
02:16:06,670 --> 02:16:09,610
never scolds his kids or yells at them.

3028
02:16:09,610 --> 02:16:12,780
If they don't have manjyuu what else were you supposed to get?

3029
02:16:14,340 --> 02:16:15,680
I'm tired.

3030
02:16:15,680 --> 02:16:16,880
She has decided not to go.

3031
02:16:17,050 --> 02:16:19,720
He knows what she's trying to do.

3032
02:16:23,190 --> 02:16:23,990
Achoo.

3033
02:16:23,990 --> 02:16:25,090
What a nice sound

3034
02:16:25,060 --> 02:16:26,360
Nice old man.

3035
02:16:28,890 --> 02:16:33,260
We appreciate the gloves but we would also really like to eat some manjyuu.

3036
02:16:33,900 --> 02:16:37,000
Riri, thank you for the gloves.

3037
02:16:37,000 --> 02:16:38,740
But with the tea

3038
02:16:38,740 --> 02:16:42,740
I would like to eat some manjyuu. Please, Riri.

3039
02:16:45,110 --> 02:16:46,480
And with that...

3040
02:16:46,980 --> 02:16:49,550
Ririka, let's go outside.

3041
02:16:48,350 --> 02:16:49,550
Yeah, please go.

3042
02:16:49,550 --> 02:16:51,320
Let's take a break.

3043
02:16:51,320 --> 02:16:53,420
Trying to change her mood.

3044
02:16:53,780 --> 02:16:56,390
We are both pretty tired.

3045
02:16:57,150 --> 02:17:01,530
Since I play guitar my fingers are crucial.

3046
02:17:01,730 --> 02:17:05,800
You can just use a pick instead.

3047
02:17:03,960 --> 02:17:05,800
I see.

3048
02:17:05,800 --> 02:17:08,330
Then it won't be a problem.

3049
02:17:06,860 --> 02:17:08,330
What about this hand?

3050
02:17:08,330 --> 02:17:11,970
If the fingers on this hand are hurt then it will ruin the sound.

3051
02:17:11,970 --> 02:17:13,670
She lost the argument.

3052
02:17:14,870 --> 02:17:17,140
That's why they are needed.

3053
02:17:17,310 --> 02:17:18,840
What will you do if I trip and fall?

3054
02:17:18,840 --> 02:17:20,210
Then I will apply a bandage.

3055
02:17:21,780 --> 02:17:24,210
Ririka won't fall over.

3056
02:17:25,020 --> 02:17:27,880
I didn't know which type of bandage to get.

3057
02:17:27,880 --> 02:17:31,920
Ask a store worker loudly?

3058
02:17:30,150 --> 02:17:31,920
Eh?

3059
02:17:34,560 --> 02:17:39,300
I can't use a loud voice.

3060
02:17:35,930 --> 02:17:39,300
Then use a quiet voice.

3061
02:17:38,100 --> 02:17:39,830
Trying his best to reason with her.

3062
02:17:39,300 --> 02:17:41,900
Since it's you, Ririka, you can do it.

3063
02:17:39,900 --> 02:17:41,900
I feel like eating dango all of a sudden.

3064
02:17:41,900 --> 02:17:44,000
Then please go and buy some dango.

3065
02:17:44,000 --> 02:17:47,240
When mama is done I can go with her.

3066
02:17:47,240 --> 02:17:51,440
Then it will be late and everyone here will go home.

3067
02:17:49,910 --> 02:17:52,140
Seems hard.

3068
02:17:51,540 --> 02:17:56,780
Their conversation outside has been going on for 30 minutes.

3069
02:17:56,980 --> 02:18:02,820
Your extended family members are all doing their best with the Kaki. What about you, Ririka?

3070
02:18:04,090 --> 02:18:05,990
Ririka...

3071
02:18:06,760 --> 02:18:11,760
Her fathers insistence isn't wavering. He's stubborn.

3072
02:18:14,430 --> 02:18:16,230
What's that?

3073
02:18:17,230 --> 02:18:19,600
It's the drone filming them.

3074
02:18:19,600 --> 02:18:21,770
It's going away.

3075
02:18:20,840 --> 02:18:23,040
Oh no, I've been found out.

3076
02:18:23,040 --> 02:18:25,610
It's escaping.

3077
02:18:24,170 --> 02:18:26,240
Escaping.

3078
02:18:28,150 --> 02:18:29,880
Yeah, that's concerning.

3079
02:18:29,980 --> 02:18:32,450
Sorry for intruding.

3080
02:18:32,950 --> 02:18:34,990
Ririka, can you read this?

3081
02:18:34,990 --> 02:18:40,320
You can do it. Yes, you can. You can do your best.

3082
02:18:40,320 --> 02:18:42,530
Let's go!

3083
02:18:41,260 --> 02:18:42,490
Finally.

3084
02:18:41,600 --> 02:18:43,380
Remarkable.

3085
02:18:42,530 --> 02:18:44,260
Yes, you can do it.

3086
02:18:44,260 --> 02:18:45,200
Can you go?

3087
02:18:45,200 --> 02:18:46,530
And what if it rains?

3088
02:18:46,530 --> 02:18:48,130
Doesn't look like it will.

3089
02:18:48,130 --> 02:18:50,130
She's still making excuses.

3090
02:18:51,900 --> 02:18:54,370
Off I go.

3091
02:18:52,670 --> 02:18:54,370
Off you go.

3092
02:18:54,370 --> 02:18:56,370
Just like her father insisted.

3093
02:18:56,370 --> 02:18:59,510
She's on her second errand.

3094
02:18:59,510 --> 02:19:02,180
She's getting snacks for the 3 O'clock tea.

3095
02:19:02,180 --> 02:19:06,050
And bandages to protect her guitar playing father.

3096
02:19:13,620 --> 02:19:15,860
She's playing an instrument.

3097
02:19:19,300 --> 02:19:22,300
I was about to think that she wouldn't go.

3098
02:19:22,300 --> 02:19:25,440
You did well in revving her engine.

3099
02:19:25,440 --> 02:19:28,710
And her fathers new original song: "The road of kaki leaves".

3100
02:19:28,710 --> 02:19:32,940
It's a song born from the image of Ririka walking on her errand.

3101
02:20:04,740 --> 02:20:07,880
I can do it. I can do my best.

3102
02:20:07,110 --> 02:20:08,550
Do your best.

3103
02:20:07,910 --> 02:20:11,680
Can she ask the store worker this time?

3104
02:20:11,350 --> 02:20:12,820
Please do your best.

3105
02:20:12,950 --> 02:20:14,820
Where do you have dango?

3106
02:20:14,820 --> 02:20:16,320
She asked without hesitation.

3107
02:20:16,520 --> 02:20:19,120
Did you come to buy dango? Come with me.

3108
02:20:19,990 --> 02:20:23,430
I'm sorry but we've run out today. What to do? Will this do?

3109
02:20:23,430 --> 02:20:25,400
That's right. This one will do.

3110
02:20:25,400 --> 02:20:27,160
How many?

3111
02:20:27,160 --> 02:20:28,570
Six.

3112
02:20:27,800 --> 02:20:28,570
Six?

3113
02:20:28,930 --> 02:20:30,330
We are preparing kaki.

3114
02:20:30,330 --> 02:20:32,540
You are preparing Kaki at home today?

3115
02:20:32,740 --> 02:20:34,700
I see, I see. Then you need 6 indeed.

3116
02:20:34,700 --> 02:20:37,340
Even with a quiet voice she was able to convey it.

3117
02:20:38,010 --> 02:20:41,580
Since so many of her extended family have come.

3118
02:20:41,810 --> 02:20:44,580
Will you be fine if you get 4 of those and 2 of these?

3119
02:20:44,710 --> 02:20:46,020
Are you be fine with that?

3120
02:20:46,020 --> 02:20:48,950
She goes for it at her own discretion.

3121
02:20:48,950 --> 02:20:51,690
The store worker is hurrying towards the checkout.

3122
02:20:51,690 --> 02:20:53,490
She better mention the other thing.

3123
02:20:53,490 --> 02:20:55,490
And bandages.

3124
02:20:54,560 --> 02:20:55,490
Bandages?

3125
02:20:55,490 --> 02:20:57,260
She was able to say it.

3126
02:20:58,700 --> 02:21:00,700
This is a bulk pack. Is that fine?

3127
02:21:00,900 --> 02:21:04,730
Will you get this then? It has 100.

3128
02:21:04,730 --> 02:21:06,100
100 bandages?

3129
02:21:06,100 --> 02:21:09,710
I don't have the money for 100.

3130
02:21:07,800 --> 02:21:09,710
You don't have the money?

3131
02:21:09,870 --> 02:21:12,180
How many do you need?

3132
02:21:12,180 --> 02:21:13,110
Just one?

3133
02:21:13,610 --> 02:21:15,750
We don't sell just one.

3134
02:21:15,750 --> 02:21:22,050
You see... While it has 100 bandages in the pack it only costs 149 Yen.

3135
02:21:21,050 --> 02:21:23,220
That's cheap.

3136
02:21:22,390 --> 02:21:24,020
It's this cheap?

3137
02:21:24,020 --> 02:21:25,860
Will you get it then?

3138
02:21:25,860 --> 02:21:28,330
That's 628 Yen.

3139
02:21:28,330 --> 02:21:31,430
The bandages are for papa, right?

3140
02:21:31,760 --> 02:21:34,600
He plays guitar.

3141
02:21:34,600 --> 02:21:36,200
He plays guitar?

3142
02:21:35,500 --> 02:21:38,600
She's regaining her confidence.

3143
02:21:36,200 --> 02:21:40,200
Is it because he plays guitar that he needs to protect his fingers?

3144
02:21:40,200 --> 02:21:43,440
So he will use them to protect his fingers?

3145
02:21:44,670 --> 02:21:45,840
You are a bright child.

3146
02:21:45,840 --> 02:21:49,380
Please take this to papa, your mama and family members.

3147
02:21:49,380 --> 02:21:51,720
Thank you very much.

3148
02:21:51,720 --> 02:21:54,620
Even from behind she's beaming with confidence.

3149
02:21:54,620 --> 02:21:56,950
A huge difference from last time she came.

3150
02:22:03,590 --> 02:22:07,660
She was able to. She did it. She did her best.

3151
02:22:24,510 --> 02:22:27,080
A satisfied face.

3152
02:22:40,460 --> 02:22:45,240
She's walking back on the same road as before but there's a big difference.

3153
02:22:46,270 --> 02:22:49,670
Ririka loves the kaki season.

3154
02:22:49,670 --> 02:22:54,840
Because that's the season her father is home instead of away on the usual live tours.

3155
02:22:55,250 --> 02:22:57,750
Her father is waiting.

3156
02:22:57,750 --> 02:23:01,120
He's wondering about her face when she opens the door.

3157
02:23:06,020 --> 02:23:08,190
Welcome back.

3158
02:23:06,520 --> 02:23:08,190
This face.

3159
02:23:08,430 --> 02:23:11,860
Welcome back.
Thank you.

3160
02:23:12,530 --> 02:23:13,860
Amazingly quick.

3161
02:23:13,860 --> 02:23:16,370
She made it for the 3 O'clock break.

3162
02:23:16,370 --> 02:23:18,870
You got lots of green manjyuu.

3163
02:23:19,100 --> 02:23:20,670
They only had four.

3164
02:23:20,670 --> 02:23:23,270
I see. But you were able to ask the store worker.

3165
02:23:23,270 --> 02:23:25,510
But it was with a quiet voice, though.

3166
02:23:25,980 --> 02:23:27,880
How amazing.

3167
02:23:27,880 --> 02:23:31,750
Thank you. Let's have some tea.

3168
02:23:32,620 --> 02:23:34,850
Enjoy these manjyuu.

3169
02:23:35,320 --> 02:23:38,760
Everyone, thank you for your hard work.

3170
02:23:37,350 --> 02:23:38,760
Thanks for the treat.

3171
02:23:39,020 --> 02:23:43,230
Thank you. You purchased these?

3172
02:23:43,360 --> 02:23:45,030
Delicious.

3173
02:23:45,030 --> 02:23:47,200
How great.

3174
02:23:47,900 --> 02:23:50,770
This is also a break to appreciate the work of Ririka.

3175
02:23:50,100 --> 02:23:52,870
That's true.

3176
02:23:50,670 --> 02:23:52,870
Is it delicious?

3177
02:23:52,870 --> 02:23:54,600
Welcome back.

3178
02:23:54,600 --> 02:23:58,270
Her pÃ¢tissier mother has returned from her job.

3179
02:23:58,270 --> 02:23:59,980
What did you do?

3180
02:23:59,980 --> 02:24:01,180
I went shopping.

3181
02:24:01,180 --> 02:24:02,610
Only once?

3182
02:24:02,610 --> 02:24:04,110
You went twice? Why?

3183
02:24:04,110 --> 02:24:07,180
There's so much she wants to tell her mother.

3184
02:24:07,180 --> 02:24:09,250
Let's go.

3185
02:24:08,320 --> 02:24:09,250
You see.

3186
02:24:09,390 --> 02:24:12,020
Daddy is so stubborn.

